---
/**
 * Hero "3D" scene — a CSS/SVG planet with an orbiting, tilted text ring.
 *
 * All motion (ring spin, intro scale, scroll parallax) is driven by browser-only
 * code in /public/site.js, which runs exclusively on the client. Nothing here
 * touches window/document during the static build, so SSG stays safe. This is the
 * isolation seam described in the architecture brief: to swap in a heavy WebGL /
 * Three.js scene with progressive .glb (Draco) loading later, replace this markup
 * with a `client:only` island — the surrounding layout and styles stay untouched.
 */
---
<div id="planet-scene" aria-hidden="true">
  <svg class="ps-textring" viewBox="0 0 500 500">
    <defs><path id="ptcircle" d="M 250,250 m -150,0 a 150,150 0 1,1 300,0 a 150,150 0 1,1 -300,0"></path></defs>
    <text textLength="942" lengthAdjust="spacingAndGlyphs"><textPath href="#ptcircle" startOffset="0">BRANDING ✳ DESIGN ✳ MARKETING ✳ SCALE HOUZ ✳ </textPath></text>
  </svg>
  <div class="planet"></div>
</div>
